.cm This draws an 8x10" border on the page, then lets you select the FILL
.cm pattern for that border.  Use the FONTASY command:	  .RD BORDER.KEY
.cm		{".CM" means "comment", and FONTASY ignores it}
.cm
.xy 0,0 	{start at upper-left corner of page)
.cm		{next line starts a rectangle and moves to lower-right corner}
.ke alt r ctl right ctl pgdn
.xy +0,-72	{stay at extreme right, but move UP one inch for clearance}
.cm		{next line finalizes the rectangle}
.ke f9
.xy -60,-36	{this gives a 1/2 inch border on an IBM or Epson}
.cm		{next line starts the inner rectangle of the border}
.ke alt r
.xy 60,36	{you can change the 60/36 for other printers}
.cm		{next line finalizes the 2nd rectangle and goes into FILL}
.ke f9 left alt f
